#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.187"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.187:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.187:0.2"
msgid "19. Brāhmaṇavagga "
msgstr "19. Brahmins "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.187:0.3"
msgid "187. Vassakārasutta "
msgstr "187. With Vassakāra "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.187:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.187:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho vassakāro brāhmaṇo magadhamahāmatto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then Vassakāra the brahmin, a chief minister of Magadha, went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "an4.187:1.3"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vassakāro brāhmaṇo magadhamahāmatto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.187:2.1"
msgid "“Jāneyya nu kho, bho gotama, asappuriso asappurisaṃ: "
msgstr "“Master Gotama, could a bad person know of a bad person: "

msgctxt "an4.187:2.2"
msgid "‘asappuriso ayaṃ bhavan’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This fellow is a bad person’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.187:2.3"
msgid "“Aṭṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, brāhmaṇa, anavakāso yaṃ asappuriso asappurisaṃ jāneyya: "
msgstr "“That’s impossible, brahmin, it can’t happen.” "

msgctxt "an4.187:2.4"
msgid "‘asappuriso ayaṃ bhavan’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.187:2.5"
msgid "“Jāneyya pana, bho gotama, asappuriso sappurisaṃ: "
msgstr "“Could a bad person know of a good person: "

msgctxt "an4.187:2.6"
msgid "‘sappuriso ayaṃ bhavan’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This fellow is a good person’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.187:2.7"
msgid "“Etampi kho, brāhmaṇa, aṭṭhānaṃ anavakāso yaṃ asappuriso sappurisaṃ jāneyya: "
msgstr "“That too is impossible, it can’t happen.” "

msgctxt "an4.187:2.8"
msgid "‘sappuriso ayaṃ bhavan’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.187:2.9"
msgid "“Jāneyya nu kho, bho gotama, sappuriso sappurisaṃ: "
msgstr "“Master Gotama, could a good person know of a good person: "

msgctxt "an4.187:2.10"
msgid "‘sappuriso ayaṃ bhavan’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This fellow is a good person’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.187:2.11"
msgid "“Ṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, brāhmaṇa, vijjati yaṃ sappuriso sappurisaṃ jāneyya: "
msgstr "“That, brahmin, is possible.” "

msgctxt "an4.187:2.12"
msgid "‘sappuriso ayaṃ bhavan’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.187:2.13"
msgid "“Jāneyya pana, bho gotama, sappuriso asappurisaṃ: "
msgstr "“Could a good person know of a bad person: "

msgctxt "an4.187:2.14"
msgid "‘asappuriso ayaṃ bhavan’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This fellow is a bad person’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.187:2.15"
msgid "“Etampi kho, brāhmaṇa, ṭhānaṃ vijjati yaṃ sappuriso asappurisaṃ jāneyya: "
msgstr "“That too is possible.” "

msgctxt "an4.187:2.16"
msgid "‘asappuriso ayaṃ bhavan’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.180, sc3
msgctxt "an4.187:3.1"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, bho gotama, abbhutaṃ, bho gotama. "
msgstr "“It’s incredible, Master Gotama, it’s amazing, "

msgctxt "an4.187:3.2"
msgid "Yāva subhāsitañcidaṃ bhotā gotamena: "
msgstr "how well said this was by Master Gotama: "

msgctxt "an4.187:3.3"
msgid "‘aṭṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, brāhmaṇa, anavakāso yaṃ asappuriso asappurisaṃ jāneyya—"
msgstr "‘It’s impossible, it can’t happen, that a bad person could know … "

msgctxt "an4.187:3.4"
msgid "asappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.187:3.5"
msgid "Etampi kho, brāhmaṇa, aṭṭhānaṃ anavakāso yaṃ asappuriso sappurisaṃ jāneyya—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.187:3.6"
msgid "sappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.187:3.7"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, brāhmaṇa, vijjati yaṃ sappuriso sappurisaṃ jāneyya—"
msgstr "But it is possible that a good person could know …’ "

msgctxt "an4.187:3.8"
msgid "sappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.187:3.9"
msgid "Etampi kho, brāhmaṇa, ṭhānaṃ vijjati yaṃ sappuriso asappurisaṃ jāneyya—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.187:3.10"
msgid "asappuriso ayaṃ bhavan’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.187:4.1"
msgid "Ekamidaṃ, bho gotama, samayaṃ todeyyassa brāhmaṇassa parisati parūpārambhaṃ vattenti: "
msgstr "Once, members of the brahmin Todeyya’s assembly were going on complaining about others: "

msgctxt "an4.187:4.2"
msgid "‘bālo ayaṃ rājā eḷeyyo samaṇe rāmaputte abhippasanno, samaṇe ca pana rāmaputte evarūpaṃ paramanipaccakāraṃ karoti, yadidaṃ abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ añjalikammaṃ sāmīcikammanti. "
msgstr "‘This King Eḷeyya is a fool to be so devoted to Rāmaputta. He even shows him the utmost deference by bowing down to him, rising up for him, greeting him with joined palms, and observing proper etiquette for him. "

msgctxt "an4.187:4.3"
msgid "Imepi rañño eḷeyyassa parihārakā bālā—"
msgstr "And these king’s men are fools too—"

#. VAR: moggallo → puggalo (mr)
msgctxt "an4.187:4.4"
msgid "yamako moggallo uggo nāvindakī gandhabbo aggivesso, ye samaṇe rāmaputte abhippasannā, samaṇe ca pana rāmaputte evarūpaṃ paramanipaccakāraṃ karonti, yadidaṃ abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ añjalikammaṃ sāmīcikamman’ti. "
msgstr "Yamaka, Moggalla, Ugga, Nāvindakī, Gandhabba, and Aggivessa—for they show the same kind of deference to Rāmaputta.’ "

msgctxt "an4.187:4.5"
msgid "Tyāssudaṃ todeyyo brāhmaṇo iminā nayena neti. "
msgstr "Then the brahmin Todeyya reasoned with them like this: "

msgctxt "an4.187:4.6"
msgid "‘Taṃ kiṃ maññanti, bhonto, "
msgstr "‘What do you think, sirs? "

msgctxt "an4.187:4.7"
msgid "paṇḍito rājā eḷeyyo karaṇīyādhikaraṇīyesu vacanīyādhivacanīyesu alamatthadasatarehi alamatthadasataro’ti? "
msgstr "When it comes to the various duties and speeches, isn’t King Eḷeyya astute, even better than the experts?’ "

msgctxt "an4.187:4.8"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, bho, paṇḍito rājā eḷeyyo karaṇīyādhikaraṇīyesu vacanīyādhivacanīyesu alamatthadasatarehi alamatthadasataroti. "
msgstr "‘That’s true, sir.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.187:5.1"
msgid "Yasmā ca kho, bho, samaṇo rāmaputto raññā eḷeyyena paṇḍitena paṇḍitataro karaṇīyādhikaraṇīyesu vacanīyādhivacanīyesu alamatthadasatarena alamatthadasataro, tasmā rājā eḷeyyo samaṇe rāmaputte abhippasanno, samaṇe ca pana rāmaputte evarūpaṃ paramanipaccakāraṃ karoti, yadidaṃ abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ añjalikammaṃ sāmīcikammaṃ’. "
msgstr "‘It’s because Rāmaputta is even more astute and expert than King Eḷeyya that the king is so devoted to him. That’s why he even shows Rāmaputta the utmost deference by bowing down to him, rising up for him, greeting him with joined palms, and observing proper etiquette for him. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.181, sc6
msgctxt "an4.187:6.1"
msgid "‘Taṃ kiṃ maññanti, bhonto, "
msgstr "What do you think, sirs? "

msgctxt "an4.187:6.2"
msgid "paṇḍitā rañño eḷeyyassa parihārakā—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.187:6.3"
msgid "yamako moggallo uggo nāvindakī gandhabbo aggivesso, karaṇīyādhikaraṇīyesu vacanīyādhivacanīyesu alamatthadasatarehi alamatthadasatarā’ti? "
msgstr "When it comes to the various duties and speeches, aren’t the king’s men—Yamaka, Moggalla, Ugga, Nāvindakī, Gandhabba, and Aggivessa—astute, even better than the experts?’ "

msgctxt "an4.187:6.4"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, bho, paṇḍitā rañño eḷeyyassa parihārakā—"
msgstr "‘That’s true, sir.’ "

msgctxt "an4.187:6.5"
msgid "yamako moggallo uggo nāvindakī gandhabbo aggivesso, karaṇīyādhikaraṇīyesu vacanīyādhivacanīyesu alamatthadasatarehi alamatthadasatarāti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an4.187:7.1"
msgid "Yasmā ca kho, bho, samaṇo rāmaputto rañño eḷeyyassa parihārakehi paṇḍitehi paṇḍitataro karaṇīyādhikaraṇīyesu vacanīyādhivacanīyesu alamatthadasatarehi alamatthadasataro, tasmā rañño eḷeyyassa parihārakā samaṇe rāmaputte abhippasannā; "
msgstr "‘It’s because Rāmaputta is even more astute and expert than the king’s men that they have such devotion to him. … "

msgctxt "an4.187:7.2"
msgid "samaṇe ca pana rāmaputte evarūpaṃ paramanipaccakāraṃ karonti, yadidaṃ abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ añjalikammaṃ sāmīcikamman’ti. "
msgstr "It’s because Rāmaputta is even more astute and expert than King Eḷeyya that the king is so devoted to him. That’s why he even shows Rāmaputta the utmost deference by bowing down to him, rising up for him, greeting him with joined palms, and observing proper etiquette for him.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an4.187:8.1"
msgid "Acchariyaṃ, bho gotama, abbhutaṃ, bho gotama. "
msgstr "It’s incredible, Master Gotama, it’s amazing, "

msgctxt "an4.187:8.2"
msgid "Yāva subhāsitañcidaṃ bhotā gotamena: "
msgstr "how well said this was by Master Gotama: "

msgctxt "an4.187:8.3"
msgid "‘aṭṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, brāhmaṇa, anavakāso yaṃ asappuriso asappurisaṃ jāneyya—"
msgstr "‘It’s impossible, it can’t happen, that a bad person could know … "

msgctxt "an4.187:8.4"
msgid "asappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.187:8.5"
msgid "Etampi kho, brāhmaṇa, aṭṭhānaṃ anavakāso yaṃ asappuriso sappurisaṃ jāneyya—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.187:8.6"
msgid "sappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.187:8.7"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, brāhmaṇa, vijjati yaṃ sappuriso sappurisaṃ jāneyya—"
msgstr "But it is possible that a good person could know … "

msgctxt "an4.187:8.8"
msgid "sappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.187:8.9"
msgid "Etampi kho, brāhmaṇa, ṭhānaṃ vijjati yaṃ sappuriso asappurisaṃ jāneyya—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.187:8.10"
msgid "asappuriso ayaṃ bhavan’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.187:8.11"
msgid "Handa ca dāni mayaṃ, bho gotama, gacchāma. "
msgstr "Well, now, Master Gotama, I must go. "

msgctxt "an4.187:8.12"
msgid "Bahukiccā mayaṃ bahukaraṇīyā”ti. "
msgstr "I have many duties, and much to do.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.187:8.13"
msgid "“Yassadāni tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, kālaṃ maññasī”ti. "
msgstr "“Please, brahmin, go at your convenience.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an4.187:9.1"
msgid "Atha kho vassakāro brāhmaṇo magadhamahāmatto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmīti. "
msgstr "Then Vassakāra the brahmin, having approved and agreed with what the Buddha said, got up from his seat and left. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.187:9.2"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

